The Task is to create a website with the flask framework.
(Documentation can be found at https://flask.palletsprojects.com)

1. install the flask framework
2. Create a simple Hello World! Page
3. Display a simple html file
4. Modify the style via css
5. Implement some html code via jinja2
6. Create html data in the displayed html file depending on the url
7. Create a quiz input form asking a simple question

Advice
Check out http://flask.pocoo.org/

Hints:
Start by reading https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/quickstart/#a-minimal-application

2. You can simply return a string containing some HTML
3. Open and read the contents of a HTML file, then return them
4. Save a stylesheet.css according to https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/quickstart/#static-files
    and reference it inside your HTML file
5. Read https://jinja.palletsprojects.com/en/3.1.x/templates/ to learn about Jinja
    and https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/quickstart/#rendering-templates
    to Äºearn how to use it with Flask.
    start by simply displaying a variable in HTML
6. Look at how to pass values through URLs
    (Example https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/quickstart/#rendering-templates)
7. Read about how to create a HTML form and how to use it with flask
    (https://flask.palletsprojects.com/en/2.3.x/quickstart/#the-request-object)

Challenge
Implement a way to create a form to upload files to the server
